<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Le Duc Anh Receives Lao Army Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Le Duc Anh Receives Lao Army Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2505153194 Hanoi VNA in English 1420 GMT 25 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2505153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA May 25 -- President Le Duc Anh received 
here today a delegation of the General Political Department of 
the Lao People's Army (LPA) led by Sr. Lt. Gen Siphon Phalikhan, 
member of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party (LPRP) Central 
Committee, vice minister of national defence, and chairman of 
the General Political Department of the LPA, now on a visit to 
Vietnam. 
  Among those present at the reception was Sr. Lt. Gen Le Kha 
Phieu, Politburo member and secretary of the Communist Party of 
Vietnam (CPV) Central Committee and chairman of the General 
Political Department of the Vietnam People's Army (VPA). 
  During the reception, General Phalikhan expressed his 
pleasure at the VPA's constant growth, thus contributing to the 
achievements recorded by the Vietnamese people in the current 
renovation process. This, he said, is the source of 
encouragement and precious experience for the Lao people in 
general and the LPA in particular in the reconstruction and 
defence of their country. 
  President Le Duc Anh, for his part, expressed his desire to 
strengthen the exchange of activities between the two countries 
in various fields, thus contributing to further consolidating 
and developing the friendship and special cooperation between 
the two peoples. 

</TEXT>

