<H3> <TI>   Government To Impose Trade Embargo on Haiti </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Impose Trade Embargo on Haiti </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2505095694 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 24 May 
94 Morning Edition p 5 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2505095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government announced on 23 May a decision to 
ban exports to and merchant trade with Haiti by revising part of 
the Foreign Exchange Control Order and the Export Trade Control 
Order. The measure has been taken in line with a full-scale UN 
embargo against Haiti to oust the country's military government 
from power. 
  Japan will start an import embargo against Haiti on 27 May 
after revising the orders on 24 May. 
  The government's newly decided economic sanctions against 
Haiti comprise: 1) a ban on the export of all cargoes to Haiti, 
and 2) a ban on merchant trade with Haiti. 
  Japan made the announcement following the UN Security 
Council's decision to impose a full-scale embargo against Haiti 
to urge the Haiti military government to step down and restore 
civilian rule. 
  Japanese exports to Haiti in 1993 were worth about 600 
million yen. 

</TEXT>

