<H3> <TI>   Defense Officials To Solve DPRK Issue by Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Officials To Solve DPRK Issue by Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2005041794 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 20 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2005041794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From MAINICHI SHIMBUN 20 May Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Major General Lukyanov, deputy chief of the Russian 
Defense Ministry International Treaty Directorate, who is on a 
visit to Japan, met Ken Sato, defense councilor, at the Defense 
Agency [DA] on 19 May. They discussed the DPRK's suspected 
development of nuclear arms, and agreed that this problem should 
be resolved through dialogue. This is the first time Japanese 
and Russian defense officials have shared a common view on the 
North Korean issue. 
  Sato also suggested a visit to Moscow by Naoaki Murata, 
director general of the DA Defense Policy Bureau, in 1994. 
Lukyanov agreed in principle. Exchanges between the two 
countries on defense matters started two years ago at the 
councilor level. [If Murata's visit materializes,] this will be 
the first exchange at the bureau director general level. 

</TEXT>

