<H3> <TI>   UK Asks Tokyo To Halt Yen Loans to Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK Asks Tokyo To Halt Yen Loans to Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2105190794 Tokyo TOKYO SHIMBUN in Japanese 20 May 94 
Morning Edition p 3 </F>



<TEXT>
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY 
<F P=103> OW2105190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo TOKYO SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>
BFN 

  [Text] On 19 May, a Foreign Ministry source said the UK 
has asked Japan through diplomatic channels to stop extending 
yen loans to Iran. Japan resumed yen loan programs to Iran 
starting in May 1993. The UK has made the request for reasons 
such as Iran's support for terrorist activities conducted by 
radical groups that advocate Islamic Fundamentalism. 
  The UK is the second nation, following the United States, to 
ask Japan to stop extending yen loans to Iran. The Japanese 
Government has judged that it has become increasingly likely 
that the Iranian issue will be a key topic at the July Naples 
summit. It has therefore made firm its plan to stop extending 
yen loans to Iran for this year, tentatively until the 
conclusion of the Naples summit. 
  However, depending on the outcome of the Naples summit, it 
can be expected that the government may face further difficulty 
regarding the second phase of yen loans to Iran. The government 
is likely to be pressed to make a difficult political decision 
on whether or not to continue extending yen loans to Iran. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

