<H3> <TI>   Air Force Prepares Study for `State of Emergency' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force Prepares Study for `State of Emergency' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2505040694 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 24 May 94 
Morning Edition p 1 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2505040694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In answering questions posed by Mr. Shun Oide of 
the opposition Socialist Democratic Party of Japan during the 23 
May session of the House of Representative Budget Committee, 
Naoaki Murata, director of the Bureau of Defense Policy at the 
Defense Agency, disclosed that the Air Self-Defense Force [ASDF] 
has been studying the "ASDF Action Program, Part 11" to prepare 
Japan for a state of emergency. 
  During the session, Mr. Oide asked the Defense Agency 
official to present the Diet with materials on the ASDF Action 
Program, Part 11. In response, Mr. Murata said: "The ASDF has 
not been working on the study on the premise of amending the 
Self-Defense Forces Law, and I would like to refrain from 
presenting to the Diet any materials which reveal military 
operations." Mr. Oide refused to relent and demanded that the 
question be discussed at the council meeting of the Budget 
Committee. 
  According to a Defense Agency official, the three services 
of 
the Self-Defense Forces have been working on studying military 
operations in anticipation of various emergency situations, but 
the substance of their study has not been made public. 

</TEXT>

