<H3> <TI>   Official on Need To Monitor U.S. Farm Bill </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official on Need To Monitor U.S. Farm Bill </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2705094594 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 27 May 94 p 21 </F>
<F P=103> BK2705094594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok BANGKOK POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Cairns group agreed in its latest meeting in 
Uruguay that the drafting of the United States Farm Bill in 
September should be monitored closely, according to 
secretary-general of the Agricultural Economics Office 
Phithiphong Phungbun na Ayutthaya. 
  He said yesterday that monitoring was necessary because of 
speculation that the US might resort to rice subsidies counter 
to the GATT agreement signed in Marrakech by GATT members 
including the US. 
  The Cairns group has assigned Canada and Australia to 
monitor 
the bill. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Suphachai Phanitchaphak proposed in 
Montevideo Uruguay, on May 19 and 20 that the agricultural 
policy of developed countries including the US, Japan and those 
in the European Union be monitored closely. 
  Developments on this issue must be reported promptly and the 
Cairns Group should ensure that developed countries refrain from 
using health regulations as trade protectionism in disguise, 
according to Thailand. 
  Thailand wants the group to push for trade in fishery 
products to be more liberalised under GATT. 

</TEXT>

