<F P=106> [From the "Intelligence" column] </F>
  [Text] Elusive Khmer Rouge supremo Pol Pot has moved house 
again. Khmer Rouge [KR] defectors reported that after spending 
some time in a special residence in Phnum Chhat area near the 
Thai border in late 1993, Pol Pot moved to the safety of 
Thailand. He is believed to living in a well-guarded compound 
inside a durian plantation near the provincial capital, 
Chanthaburi. For a number of years in the late 1980s, Pol Pot 
had lived in a compound called "Zone 87" in Trat province 
bordering Cambodia. 

