<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bulgaria's Daskalov Arrives, Meets Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bulgaria's Daskalov Arrives, Meets Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Daskalov Backs `Tough Approach' for Peace </H4>

<F P=102> AU2904091894 Prague CTK in English 1930 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2904091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 28 (CTK) -- Bulgarian-Czech relations 
were appreciated as good by Czech Parliament Chairman Milan Uhde 
and visiting Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov at 
their meeting today. Uhde and Daskalov welcomed the signing of 
an agreement on cooperation between the two countries' foreign 
ministries and the fact that agreements on the prevention of 
double taxation and on investment protection were under 
preparation, Uhde told CTK after the meeting. 
  Regarding the conflict in the former Yugoslavia Daskalov 
voiced the view that tough approach towards all who violate 
peace in the region should be adopted and that the United 
States, Russia, and NATO should equally participate in solving 
the situation. Daskalov also met Czech Premier Vaclav Klaus 
today. 

</TEXT>

