<H3> <TI>   Klaus Downplays Austria's Anti-Temelin Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Klaus Downplays Austria's Anti-Temelin Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804201394 Prague CTK in English 1800 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2804201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 28 (CTK) -- The activity of Austrian 
politicians concerning the completion of the Temelin nuclear 
power plant in south Bohemia should not be seen as a threat to 
or violation of the Czech Republic's sovereignty, Czech Premier 
Vaclav Klaus told Parliament today. 
  He said steps taken on the issue by some Austrian 
politicians 
should not serve as a reason for the Czech diplomacy to resort 
to resolute actions the consequences of which might hamper the 
Czech Republic's relations with Austria. 
  Czech-Austrian relations in the power industry are defined 
by 
a Czech-Austrian agreement on nuclear security and protection 
against radiation. According to the agreement, experts from 
both countries meet annually and Austrian representatives are 
informed on all Czech goals concerning the use of nuclear power. 

</TEXT>

