<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   MDF `Deeply Indignant' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MDF `Deeply Indignant' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804163894 Budapest MTI in English 1408 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2804163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 28 April (MTI) -- The presidium of the 
ruling Hungarian Democratic Forum (MDF) voiced its satisfaction 
in Budapest today that most political parties conduct their 
election campaigns according to European norms, disproving fears 
of the campaign becoming dirty, MDF spokesman Karoly Herenyi 
told a news conference after the presidium session. Answering 
questions from the press, Herenyi denied that his party is 
carrying on a negative campaign. 
  Herenyi also said the MDF is "deeply indignant" at attempts 
to revive the fascist arrow-cross and Hungarist movement. The 
MDF presidium has called upon the state prosecutors office to do 
all it can to ban these organizations. At the same time, the 
presidium also cautioned against the resurgence of the extreme 
left. 
  Herenyi said the presidium has learnt from local MDF 
organizations that groupings even more extreme than the Workers' 
Party, such as members of the former Workers' Militia, hold 
regular meetings, disturbing and intimidating people in many 
places. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

