<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 28 April (MTI) -- The Hungarian Justice 
and Life Party (MIEP) considers the Hungarist Movement, its 
leaders, and particularly their statements declaring sympathy 
for the MIEP, to be clear provocations, said MIEP Co-Chairman 
Istvan Csurka at the party's press conference in Budapest on 
Thursday [28 April]. Csurka sees this as a dirty political 
trick, and said the organization is backed by forces who are 
interested in presenting the MIEP as an extreme rightist party. 
  As reported on Wednesday [27 April], leaders of the 
Hungarist 
Movement, which openly professes extreme rightist ideas, held a 
press conference in Budapest. Present were the chairmen of the 
three political groups that set up the movement: the Federation 
of Persecutees of Communism, the Hungarian National Front, and 
the World National Popular Rule Party. 
  National Front head, Istvan Gyorkos, announced at 
yesterday's 
press conference that the Hungarist program coincides with that 
of the Hungarian Justice and Life Party at several points. 

</TEXT>

