<H3> <TI>   Boross Rules Out MDF-MSZP Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Boross Rules Out MDF-MSZP Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904110894 Budapest MTI in English 2021 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2904110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 28 April (MTI) -- The Hungarian 
Democratic Forum (MDF) does not wish to deceive voters, which is 
why it clearly states the political forces with which it 
definitely does not wish to enter into a coalition, under any 
circumstances, Hungarian Prime Minister Peter Boross, deputy 
chairman of the MDF, said on Thursday [28 April], at an election 
rally held in Budapest. 
  Among these forces, Boross mentioned the Hungarian Socialist 
Party (MSZP) in the first place, and said the Socialists 
themselves had firmly ruled out the MDF a few days ago. The MDF 
also does not want to enter into a coalition with an Alliance of 
Free Democrats (SZDSZ) that is directed by the SZDSZ's strong 
core in Budapest, and which is moving closer to its one-time 
enemy, the former communists (the MSZP), Boross said. 
  The prime minister discussed in detail farming and industry. 
He also said that debt servicing, and external circumstances 
such as the collapse of the Soviet Union and its insolvency, the 
global recession, and the Balkan war have held Hungary back, 
falling short of results hoped for in the MDF's 1990 program. 

</TEXT>

