<H3> <TI>   Walesa Approves New Nomination </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Walesa Approves New Nomination </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804060294 Warsaw PAP in English 0001 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2804060294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, April 27 -- The candidature of Grzegorz W. 
Kolodko for the post of deputy prime minister and finance 
minister on Wednesday gained the approval of President Lech 
Walesa. The candidature was presented to the president by Prime 
Minister Waldemar Pawlak after the president had returned from 
Lithuania. 
  Prof. Kolodko, 45, independent, has been director of the 
Institute of Finance since 1988 and academic of the main school 
of commerce. He was an adviser to the president of the National 
Bank of Poland (NBP) during 1982-1988. Kolodko also delivered 
lectures at University of Illinois, U.S.A. In 1991 he become a 
consultant of the International Monetary Fund (IMF). In 1989 
Grzegorz Kolodko participated in the "round table" debates in 
the team for economy and social policy. 
  Kolodko, who during 1969-90 was a member of the Polish 
United 
Workers Party (PUWP), has written some 200 works on economy and 
economic policy which dealt mainly with economic growth, 
disproportions, crisis, inflation and systemic reforms. 

</TEXT>

