<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pressure To Dismiss R. Kovac `Increasing' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pressure To Dismiss R. Kovac `Increasing' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804123594 Prague CTK in English 1055 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2804123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava April 28 (CTK) -- The pressure exerted 
by the opposition on parliament to dismiss Deputy Premier Roman 
Kovac is increasing. The dismissal was proposed on Wednesday 
[27 April] by Dusan Masiar, a deputy for the Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), who is supported by 35 deputies. 
The opposition accuses Kovac of being incompetent both as 
deputy premier and from the moral point of view, and of 
corruption attempts. 
  Peter Sokol, adviser to the opposition Slovak National Party 
(SNS) said at a SNS press conference today that Kovac was 
morally incompetent mainly due to his previous "commitment". As 
deputy premier in the previous government of ex-Premier Vladimir 
Meciar, Roman Kovac was one of the protagonists of the then 
coalition agreement between the HZDS and the SNS, Sokol said. 
  According to Sokol, Kovac pushed for the joint of his post 
of 
vice-premier with the seat of health minister, and promoted 
himself to this post. 
  Parliamentary deputies refused to include the proposal to 
dismiss Roman Kovac into the agenda of the parliamentary 
session. However, Parliament Chairman Ivan Gasparovic (HZDS) 
announced he would convoke an extraordinary session to discuss 
this point immediately after the end of the current regular 
session. 
  SNS leaders also criticised former SNS leader and present 
chairman of the National Democratic Party-New Alternative 
Ludovit Cernak. 

</TEXT>

