<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moravcik on Ties With Hungary, Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moravcik on Ties With Hungary, Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804183394 Prague CTK in English 1504 GMT 28 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2804183394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 28 (CTK) -- If Hungary's 
relations with Slovakia are to improve, Hungary has to allay 
Slovak concern by guaranteeing inviolability of the border with 
Slovakia, Slovak Premier Jozef Moravcik told journalists today. 
"We insist on the border's permanency since in Slovakia the 
fear that the border might be altered is a real political 
factor," Moravcik said, adding he believed an agreement on the 
issue might be concluded this year. 
  Moravcik said the meeting of the two countries' premiers 
planned for last Monday [25 April] did not take place due to 
Hungary's unwillingness to issue a joint statement on border 
inviolability. He also said that owing to his crowded schedule 
he would not attend the coming international meeting of Liberals 
at Visegrad in Hungary, where he was supposed to unofficially 
meet Hungarian Premier Peter Boross. But he added that he did 
not rule out the possibility of still meeting Boross before the 
elections. 
  Observers in Bratislava are skeptical about the meeting 
materializing in view of the Hungarian election campaign. 
Moravcik also warned that Slovak-Hungarian relations would not 
be helped by taking mutual problems to the "Balladur plan" 
meeting due to take place on May 26-27 in Paris. 
  French President [as received] Edouard Balladur has proposed 
that a conference should be held at which the twelve countries 
of the European Union, Central and East European countries, the 
United States and Canada should come together to try to resolve 
territorial and ethnic minority questions concerning the former 
Communist countries. The plan has been approved by the EU. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

