<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Many Expect HZDS To Win Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Many Expect HZDS To Win Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2704153094 Prague CTK in English 1242 GMT 27 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2704153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 27 (CTK) -- Forty-five percent of 
Slovaks believe that early elections (scheduled for September 
30-October 1) will be won by Vladimir Meciar's Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), who was dismissed [from the post of 
prime minister] in parliament in March, a poll conducted by the 
Slovak Statistical Office in April revealed. 
  Fifteen percent of Slovaks believe the victory will be 
scored 
by Peter Weiss's Democratic Left Party (SDL). The victory of 
Premier Jozef Moravcik's Democratic Union of Slovakia (DEUS) was 
predicted by five percent of those polled. 
  Twenty-two percent of Slovaks would never vote for the HZDS. 
The same number would not vote for the Christian Democratic 
Movement (KDH). The poll revealed that the two parties' 
followers are the strongest opponents of one another. 

</TEXT>

