<H3> <TI>   Trial of Albanians `Postponed' Due to Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trial of Albanians `Postponed' Due to Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2704083894 Tirana ATA in English 1205 GMT 26 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2704083894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 26 (ATA) -- The tribunal of Skopje 
had scheduled for April 25 the trial against 10 Albanians 
arrested several months ago, among who Mitat Emini, former 
secretary of the Democratic Prosperity Party, Shenasi Rexhepi, 
former assistant minister of defence in The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia [FYROM] and others. The trial has been 
postponed for May 9, 1994 due to the strike staged by defence 
attorneys. 
  The 10 Albanians are accused of the criminal act of 
"collaboration for hostile activity," the Albanian TV said in an 
information with a source from Skopje. Further on the 
information said that Macedonian means of information are 
manipulating even in the case of this trial, presenting the 
accused as heads of the Albanian Army in this republic. Their 
trial is being used for political aims on the verge of 
multinational elections, presenting the Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia endangered by them. The Albanian political parties 
in this republic considered the said trial as framed and against 
the Albanians. 

</TEXT>

