<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bukoshi Proposes Measures To Avoid War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bukoshi Proposes Measures To Avoid War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604175894 Tirana ATA in English 1016 GMT 26 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2604175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 26 (ATA) -- Premier of the republic 
of Kosova, Dr. Bujar Bukoshi, who attended the proceedings of 
the pan-European congress between April 22-24 in Ulm of Germany, 
spoke of the situation in Kosova and around it, newspaper BUJKU 
of Prishtina reported on April 25. 
  In order to avoid an outbreak of war in Kosova, which would 
be a Balkan war of unprecedented consequences, Premier Bukoshi 
proposed four measures. First, Kosova be made an international 
protectorate, secondly, Kosova be demilitarized and its 
democratic institutions be enabled to operate, thirdly, Kosova 
be included in the peace process on former Yugoslavia, and 
fourthly, the lifting of economic sanctions on Serbia also be 
conditioned by the resolution of the Kosova problem and the 
political will of its people be recognised under the right of 
the peoples' self-determination in the territory of ruined 
Yugoslavia, Premier Bukoshi said. 

</TEXT>

