<H3> <TI>   Serbian Guards Kill Albanian on FYROM Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Guards Kill Albanian on FYROM Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804160994 Tirana ATA in English 1021 GMT 27 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2804160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 26 (ATA) -- In early hours of April 
25, Serbian forces that control the border between Kosova and 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
killed the Albanian Naim Bajrami from Llashtice of Gjilan. 
Still no reports have arrived about the conditions in which 
Bajrami, father of two children, was killed. He was killed near 
the Miratovc village, the commune of Presheve. 
  The sub Council for the Defence of the Human Rights and 
Freedoms in Gjilan reports that Naim was searched by Serbian 
police while during the last week police searched his home in 
Llashtice, under the pretext of looking for arms. He was killed 
while he was leaving Kosova because of the pressures and threats 
by the Serbian police. 
  Bajrami is the second Albanian victim of the Serbian terror 
killed on the Kosova-Macedonia border since the beginning of 
this year. 

</TEXT>

