<H3> <TI>   HSP Wants Apology From Hungarian TV </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    HSP Wants Apology From Hungarian TV </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004163294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1500 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Hungarian Socialist Party [HSP] calls on the 
leader of Hungarian Television to ensure the cleanness of 
political programs in the remaining part of the election 
campaign and to suspend from their jobs the editors of the 
"Newsreel" and "Panorama" programs. Imre Szekeres, executive 
deputy chairman of the HSP, notes in a letter addressed to TV 
Deputy Chairman Gabor Nahlik that the television documentary and 
news programs contain false allegations that fulfill the 
conditions for defamation and public slander. The HSP demands 
that the editors responsible for the programs apologize publicly 
to the party and the slandered politicians, and that Deputy 
Chairman Gabor Nahlik apologize for the false accusations by 2 
May. The HSP is asking the National Election Committee to take 
a stance in connection with Hungarian Television's political 
programs; if no change occurs the party will appeal to the 
supreme state prosecutor. 

</TEXT>

