<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Claim 2,000 Turkish UN Troops Arriving </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Claim 2,000 Turkish UN Troops Arriving </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2904201494 Belgrade BORBA in Serbo-Croatian 28 Apr 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> AU2904201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade BORBA </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by D.N.: "Turkish `Blue Helmets' Are Coming"] </F>
  [Text] Skopje -- The representatives of the Democratic 
Party of Macedonian Serbs have claimed in Skopje today that 
2,000 Turkish "Blue Helmets" are being brought to Macedonia [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM]. They did not 
want to disclose where they obtained this information, saying 
only that it came "from well-informed sources." In their 
opinion the arrival of the Turks in Macedonia will be decisively 
opposed by both the Serbian and the Macedonian population. They 
assessed this deployment as an attempt to destabilize this area, 
adding that the only guarantee of peace and stability in this 
part of the Balkans was the arrival of Russian "Blue Helmets" as 
part of the UN Protection Forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

