  [Text] Two U.S. journalists were killed and one was injured 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina today. For as yet unknown reasons their 
car skidded off the Sarajevo-Mostar road and hit a mine. Brian 
Bringhton of the (Magnolia) news agency and Francis Willian 
Tomasich of the Spin agency. William Wallman of the Spin agency 
suffered slight injuries, a spokesman for the Spanish battalion 
has told HABENA in Medjugorje. An UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Forces] patrol has taken the wounded reporter to Dracevo's 
hospital. 

