<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   International `Contact Group' Holds Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    International `Contact Group' Holds Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Buha: Talks `Good Start' </H4>

<F P=102> AU2904141694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2904141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marica Lalovic] </F>
  [Text] The talks that Radovan Karadzic, president of the 
Srpska republic, and Aleksa Buha, foreign minister of the 
republic of Srpska, held with a seven-member international 
contact group, a working body for establishing peace in the 
former Bosnia-Herzegovina, ended in Pale today. 
  After the talks, which were held behind closed doors, Aleksa 
Buha, foreign minister of the republic of Srpska, and German 
representative Michael Steiner made brief statements. Steiner 
said that the group had presented its views and ideas and that 
several interesting views and positions had been presented 
during the talks. We sincerely hope that the ideas that we 
presented here will be accepted, and that will have an effect on 
the Serbian side, because our motive is to turn the situation 
toward peace, Steiner said. 
  Aleksa Buha, foreign minister of the republic of Srpska, 
said 
that the group that came to Pale today to hold talks with the 
representatives of the republic of Srpska should connect up the 
broken threads of the peace process again. The two sides 
exchanged views on that today. Our side, the Serbian side, 
wanted the contact group to note everything that has happened in 
the mean time, the bombing, the ultimatums, and the creation of 
the Croatian-Muslim federation. We wanted the peace process to 
continue with a different methodology and we informed the 
representatives of the contact group about that. 
  Buha also said that both sides share the view that a good 
start was made today and that they should continue in the same 
direction. 

</TEXT>

