<H3> <TI>   International `Contact Group' Holds Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    International `Contact Group' Holds Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Izetbegovic Sees `No Results' </H4>

<F P=102> AU2904171694 Paris AFP in English 1703 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2904171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, April 29 (AFP) -- An international 
contact group looking to mediate between the warring Bosnians 
left here Friday [29 April] amid little sign of progress. The 
nine-man group, which Friday travelled the short journey to 
Pale, east of Sarajevo, for talks with Serb leaders later 
returned for a further meeting with Bosnia's Moslem President 
Alija Izetbegovic, before flying on to Zagreb. [passage omitted] 
  In a statement after the group's departure, Izetbegovic said 
his discussions with the group had provided no results. He said 
he had set no conditions for restarting negotiations apart from 
full Serb compliance with the NATO ultimatum and ceasefire, but 
said he was not satisfied with the situation in Gorazde. There 
were Serb troops deployed in part of the three-kilometre 
(two-mile) exclusion zone dressed as police, and artillery 
remaining in the outer exclusion zone of 20 kilometres (12.5 
miles). He added that since the Bosnian Government had received 
no guarantee from the international community, the army must 
continue to defend "free" territory. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

