<H4>    Srpska Army `Sources' Comment </H4>

<F P=102> LD2904125894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1133 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Zvornik, Bratunac, 19 Apr (TANJUG) -- Muslim 
attacks and armed provocations against the republic of Srpska 
(RS) were evidently less intense and widespread today in 
comparison with the situation in recent days, a TANJUG reporter 
has found out from republic of Srpska army sources. The same 
sources interpret this as a consequence of direct activities by 
the international Contact Group, which held talks in Sarajevo 
yesterday with representatives of the Muslim leaderhip. Reasons 
for the reduced level of combat activity by the Muslim units lie 
in the international efforts to bring about a four-month 
cease-fire, something which had been demanded by the Muslim 
leadership in Sarajevo, Serbian military sources point out. This 
is explained by the need to provide a let-up for the Muslim 
formations, which also gives them enough time to prepare new 
wider attacks against the RS, some of which are already under 
way. 
  Serbian military sources say that republic of Srpska army 
units yesterday completely crushed an extremely strong two-day 
attack by the Muslim artillery and infantry units, mainly on the 
Mackov Vrh-Javorak-Neokrinje line in the Vlasic area. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

