<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Army Chief Discusses Military Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Army Chief Discusses Military Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904214294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Army General Rasim Delic, chief of the General Staff 
of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, assessed the present military 
situation in our country speaking on Bosnia-Herzegovina 
television this evening: 
  [Begin Delic recording] Enemy forces are regrouping 
throughout the Bosnia-Herzegovina front. Some foreign agencies 
are reporting about regrouping in Posavina. This started before 
their reports. Namely, armored and mechanized forces from 
Krajina have started arriving. After Gorazde, and after the 
withdrawal from the Gorazde area, they are stepping up their 
reinforcement. The goal that the aggressor forces are trying to 
realize is well known: To widen the Brcko corridor. This 
regrouping is now taking place from Gradacac to Celic, i.e., 
along the entire Posavina section of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
front. 
  Given that we have been monitoring such events and taking 
appropriate measures I do not expect that they will surprise us 
in this respect. But one should say that the situation such as 
the one in Gorazde and earlier in Sarajevo, when the UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] was only taking over the protection of 
certain territories, creates conditions for the aggressors to 
concentrate large armored and mechanized units and even 
personnel in the specific areas that they chose as the target of 
their aggression. 
  Our demand has always been for the heavy artillery, as well 
as the armored and mechanized units of the two sides to be 
placed under effective control. Unfortunately, in both Sarajevo 
and Gorazde this did not happen and consequently there is a 
danger of additional enemy involvement in some of our other 
areas, taking into account the amount of heavy technology at the 
disposal of the Serbian aggressors. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

