<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik Favors Kozyrev's Cease-Fire Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Krajisnik Favors Kozyrev's Cease-Fire Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904224894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2205 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904224894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 29 Apr (TANJUG) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, the 
president of the people's assembly of the republic of Srpska, 
told SRNA [Bosnian Serb news] agency this evening that the Serb 
side would support Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev's 
proposal on establishing a one-year cease-fire in former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and on solving disputed issues through 
arbitration. Saying that Kozyrev's initiative "deserves great 
attention," Krajisnik added that the Serb side would support it 
"if arbitration agents who will reach a just solution are 
found." Krajisnik stressed that the Serb side believed that it 
was necessary to agree on a cessation of hostilities and replace 
the war with political negotiations, but without "prejudicing 
solutions." 
  "We would be ready to accept arbitration, but the Serbs have 
had negative experiences with the work of the international 
community which has on several occasions displayed bias and 
sided with the Muslims," the president of the republic of Srpska 
assembly said. "In any event, we advocate the establishing of 
peace and talks, but without a solution being imposed on any 
side in the conflict in former Bosnia-Herzegovina," Krajisnik 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

