<H3> <TI>   Continuing Tension Reported in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Continuing Tension Reported in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Veritable Chaos Reigns' </H4>

<F P=102> AU0205111694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0205111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mustafa Kurtovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Excerpt] Fascists from nearby hills carried out 
provocations against all the defense lines on the Gorazde 
battlefield yesterday. They shelled the commune's outskirts 
fiercely, and (Zasevi) and Brdarici in particular. UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] unit members are again acting without shame 
as not a single gesture of theirs shows that they belong to 
peace forces. Thus, in cooperation with the chetnik hordes, 
they are trying to evacuate ethnic Serb citizens from the very 
town center, but at the same time they are settling the 3-km 
zone with people from Serbia and Montenegro. To what extent the 
NATO ultimatum is being respected can be seen from the fact that 
three people were wounded in the town and its suburbs yesterday. 
  A general catastrophe is reigning in Gorazde at the moment. 
People have no food, no water, and no electricity. There are no 
medicines or first-aid kits. A veritable chaos reigns here. 
  Chetniks are still positioned 200 m away from the town 
center 
and any movement by Gorazde citizens means certain death at the 
hands of snipers. Two UNHCR convoys that arrived in Gorazde 
recently can suffice for the people to survive one day at the 
most. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-54482 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu084_i_94019" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-084 </AU>
