<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Four Serbian Civilians Killed at Doboj </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Four Serbian Civilians Killed at Doboj </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0105085694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0725 GMT 1 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0105085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Banja Luka, 1 May (TANJUG) -- Three young women 
and a young man were killed this morning by shells fired from 
the well known Muslim strongholds of Matuzic and Tesanj at the 
town of Doboj. This is reported by the Serbian republic army 
first krajina corps' information service in Banja Luka. Another 
four people were seriously wounded, surgeon Milovan Miljanovic 
confirmed at the Doboj hospital. [passage omitted] After this 
morning's attack the number of people killed in Muslim attacks 
on Doboj over the past 20 days has risen to 11, with a further 
34 being wounded. All are civilians. A general alert is in 
effect in Doboj today, Easter Sunday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

