<DATE1>  29 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Muslim Attacks Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslim Attacks Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904201394 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1935 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2904201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Doboj, April 29 (TANJUG) -- Moslem forces continued 
Friday strong artillery and infantry attacks on the Serb 
settlements and positions of the army of the Bosnian Serb 
republic (R.S.) in northern Bosnia -- around the towns of Doboj 
and Teslic, the R.S. military sources set out. Artillery fire 
on Teslic caused considerable material damage, a statement said. 
It also noted that one member of a Moslem commando-terrorist 
group was liquidated and several were wounded when this group 
attempted to infiltrate the Serb territory around Teslic. All 
the Moslem attacks were repelled, and the Moslem forces forced 
to withdraw, the statement said. 
  The Serbs in Doboj have been for over a month under 
sustained 
Moslem fire and suffered high casualties among the civilian 
population. As part of a general offensive on the Serb 
territories launched in late March, the Moslems especially 
stepped up combat activity against Doboj in an attempt to cut 
the Serb corridor in northern Bosnia linking eastern and western 
parts of the R.S. 
  The Moslem forces opened antiaircraft artillery and infantry 
fire also on the positions of the R.S. army around Srbobran 
(formerly Donji Vakuf) in central Bosnia, the statement said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

